> You've had fajitas, and you've had potato wedges, but you've probably never had
> either of those things quite like this. Potatoes roast with green bell pepper,
> onion, and our signature Fajita Spice; meanwhile, you whip up some surprising
> sides (garlic mayo and fried eggs—heyo!). Wedges are topped with cheddar and
> pepper jack, then returned to the oven until melty and "nacho-esque." Everything's
> garnished with diced tomato, eggs, and mayo drizzle, then eaten straight from
> the pan for a meal that's the best of two tasty worlds.

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@red onion{1}. Slice top off @long green pepper{1}; core and deseed, then cut into
1⁄2-inch-thick rings. Dice @roma tomato{1} into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Peel and finely
chop @garlic{1%clove}.

Toss potatoes, onion, and green pepper on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Fajita Spice Blend{2%tsp} (half for 4 servings),
a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Spread veggies out in a single layer. Roast on top rack until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

== Garlic Mayo ==

Place garlic and @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until
softened, ~{20-25%seconds}. Set aside to cool.

Once cooled, stir in @mayonnaise{4%tbsp} and remaining @Fajita Spice Blend{1%tbsp}
until combined. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Fried Eggs ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium heat.
Once hot, crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove pan from heat; cover to keep warm.

== Assembly ==

Once veggies are done, carefully remove #baking sheet{} from oven.

Sprinkle @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} over veggies.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Carefully top veggies on sheet with tomato and fried eggs. Drizzle with garlic
mayo and serve directly from sheet for a family-style experience.